The python code for quicksort is as follows:

def quicksort(sequence):
  if len(sequence) > 1:
    p = partition(sequence, 1, len(sequence))
    quicksort(sequence[:p])
    quicksort(sequence[p+1:])
  return sequence

 function partition(sequence, start, end)
   pivot = sequence[start]
   i = start
   j = end - 1
   while i < j:
     while sequence[i] < pivot:
       i += 1
     while sequence[j] > pivot:
       j -= 1
     if i < j:
       sequence[i], sequence[j] = sequence[j], sequence[i]
       i += 1
       j -= 1
   return i

 Implementation of a Quicksort in python
